fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.data

Interface ICellStructure

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    IArrayType, IFetchable, IIntersection, ISource

    public interface ICellStructure
    Defines the basic API for a fixed or dynamic structure prototype that contains data cells.
    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    REFLEXE Technologies

      • createKey

        IKey createKey(int intKey)
        throws UnsupportedOperationException
        Creates a simple integer-based key. This corresponds to a common use case but is unsuitable for structures with non-integer keys or multiple keys.
        Parameters:
        intKey - the integer value of the physical key.
        Returns:
        the new key object.
        Throws:
        UnsupportedOperationException - if the cell structure requires a non-integer key or a composite key.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        createKey(java.util.Map)

      • createKey

        IKey createKey(String stringKey)
        throws UnsupportedOperationException
        Creates a simple string-based key. This corresponds to a common use case but is unsuitable for structures with non-string keys or multiple keys.

        Do not use this variant for string representations of other remote.

        Parameters:
        stringKey - the string value of the physical key.
        Returns:
        the new key object.
        Throws:
        UnsupportedOperationException - if the cell structure requires a non-string key or a composite key.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        createKey(java.util.Map)

      • createKey

        IKey createKey(UUID uuidKey)
        throws UnsupportedOperationException
        Creates a simple UUID-based key. This corresponds to some specific use cases but is unsuitable for structures with non-UUID keys or multiple keys.
        Parameters:
        uuidKey - the UUID value of the physical key.
        Returns:
        the new key object.
        Throws:
        UnsupportedOperationException - if the cell structure requires a non-UUID key or a composite key.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        createKey(java.util.Map)

      • createKey

        IKey createKey(Map<String,Object> compositeKeyValue)
        throws IllegalArgumentException
        Creates a composite key or a simple single-cell key with an appropriate supported datatype.
        Parameters:
        compositeKeyValue - a map containing cell names as keys and cell values as map values.
        Returns:
        the new key object.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the cell structure cannot create a key using the specified cell names and values.
        Since:
        1.0

      • getCell

        Gets a cell by reference to its unique identifier.
        Parameters:
        cellId - the non-null globally-unique cell identifier.
        Returns:
        the matching cell (if defined), or null.
        Since:

      • getCell

        ICell getCell(String cellName)
        Gets a cell by reference to its unique name in the context of this container.
        Parameters:
        cellName - the non-null cell name, unique in the context of this container.
        Returns:
        the matching cell (if defined), or null.
        Since:
        1.0

      • getFixedCells

        SortedSet<ICell> getFixedCells()
        Gets the ordered set of fixed cells for this source (mandatory for all items, even if values are not mandatory).
        Returns:
        the non-null (possibly empty) set of fixed cells.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        getOptionalCells(), hasDynamicCells()

      • getOptionalCells

        SortedSet<ICell> getOptionalCells()
        Gets the ordered set of optional cells for this source (may not be defined for all items). This set does not contain any fixed cells. Where possible, known dynamic cells are included, but this is not always possible (depending on the technology used by the connector).
        Returns:
        the non-null (possibly empty) set of fixed cells.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        getFixedCells(), hasDynamicCells(), IDataStructure.getExtraCells()

      • hasDynamicCells

        boolean hasDynamicCells()
        Indicates if the record source can have dynamic cells (extra cells for specific items). This is generally not the case for SQL data sources, but may be the case for other types of data source.
        Returns:
        true if different items can have different cells, otherwise false.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        IDataStructure.addCell(ICell), IDataStructure.removeCell(ICell)
